#Comments on section1:
#1.Mean, Median and Range analysis: 
#Mean analysis : Average home price in West region is maximum for all years while 
#Central region has least average home price among for all years.
#Average Home Prices were started increasing from 2004 and reached maximum price in 2007 for all four regions. 
#After 2007, prices were started decreasing with little up and down till 2012.
#Average home price in central region in 2007 was maximum (389.9) among all region in all years.
#Median analysis:Central and Southeast regions are cheap with median home price as 127 and 140 respectivley. 
#Northeast and West regions are expensive with median home price as 216.9 and 220.5 respectively.
#Range analysis:West region has highest range while Central and Southeast region have lower range.

#2.Box Plot Analysis: Central and Northeast regions have high numbers of outliers.
#Southeast and West regions do not have many outliers. Overall mean is greater than overall median for all regions.

#3.Histogram Analysis: Central, Southeast and West have right skewed distribution. 
#Northeast distribution has widely distributed skew which is close to normal.
#Home Price in west region is very expensive as the starting price is above 100 and goes beyond 800.
#Home price in Central region is very cheap as the starting price is from 75.

#3 - ANOVA  and t-tests for the key regions.  Set up your hypothesis testing and run your analysis to either reject or not to reject your null hypothesis.
#alpha=0.05
#null hypothesis: There is no significant difference between means of different regions.
#alternative hypothesis: There is significant difference between means of different regions.
results = ols('Price ~ Region', data=HomePrice_Melt).fit()
